					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13965198#post-4865085</guid>
				<title>On-site or On sight?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13965198/scp-5890#post-4865085</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 08 Jan 2021 12:31:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ShadowSpirit90</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6753095</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While reading the containment procedures, I noticed something I feel should be addressed, and it was niggling in the inside of my head until I did.</p> <p>You say that any Foundation personnel who exit SCP-5890 are to be terminated on-site.<br /> Now, does this mean that the anomaly is held on a site, and the entities are to be taken elsewhere on the site for termination, which would be &quot;on-site&quot;, or do you mean as soon as you see a Foundation personnel leaving the anomaly, they are the be immediately terminated, because that would be spelled &quot;On sight.&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13965198#post-4859696</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13965198/scp-5890#post-4859696</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 01 Jan 2021 22:13:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Uncle Nicolini</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3487700</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This piece is riddled with minor SPAG issues as well as some rather unusual and unclinical phrasing (&quot;silence can be heard&quot;?????). I found the earlier exploration logs too tame and the later ones too difficult to follow due to weird phrasings. We also barely get to know Asheworth as a character, so his journey here is two dimensional at best.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
